The paper deals with iterative approaches to density estimation and sampling, which are common topics in machine learning and statistics. The use of boosting and weak learners also suggests a focus on machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves convergence rates and assumptions, which are related to statistical theory, making cs.ST (Statistics) a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the paper mentions a variational characterization of $f$-divergences, which is a topic in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
